<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

<p>Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how NexaCore (“we,” “us,” or “our”) collects, uses, discloses, and safeguards your personal information when you visit our website and use our services.</p>

<h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> When you register, we collect your name, email address, billing address, and password.</li>
    <li><strong>Payment Information:</strong> We store only the minimum payment details (e.g. last 4 digits of your card, billing address) needed to process subscriptions; full card data is handled securely by our PCI‑compliant payment processor.</li>
    <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> We log how you interact with our platform (pages viewed, features used, timestamps) to provide and improve our service.</li>
    <li><strong>Cookies & Tracking:</strong> We use cookies and similar technologies to remember your preferences, keep you signed in, and analyze site traffic.</li>
</ul>

<h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>To Provide & Manage Services:</strong> Create your account, process subscriptions, and deliver customer support.</li>
    <li><strong>To Improve Our Platform:</strong> Analyze usage trends so we can add features, fix bugs, and optimize performance.</li>
    <li><strong>To Communicate:</strong> Send transactional emails (invoices, password resets) and, with your consent, occasional product updates and offers.</li>
    <li><strong>To Ensure Security:</strong> Detect and prevent fraud, unauthorized access, and other security threats.</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Data Sharing & Disclosure</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> We share data with trusted vendors (e.g., payment processors, hosting providers) who help us operate.</li>
    <li><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> We may disclose information to comply with laws or protect rights, safety, or property.</li>
    <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> If we merge, acquire, or sell assets, user data may be transferred—but we’ll notify you and require any new owner to respect this policy.</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Your Choices & Rights</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Access & Correction:</strong> You can view and update your account profile at any time.</li>
    <li><strong>Deleting Your Account:</strong> Contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@nexacore.com">privacy@nexacore.com</a> to request deletion. We’ll remove your personal data within 30 days, except for records we must keep for legal or accounting purposes.</li>
    <li><strong>Marketing Opt‑Out:</strong> Click “unsubscribe” in any promotional email or update your preferences in your account settings.</li>
    <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> You can block or delete cookies in your browser, though some functionality may be impaired.</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Data Security</h2>
<p>We implement industry‑standard technical and organizational measures—encryption, firewalls, access controls—to protect your data. However, no system is completely impenetrable; please help keep your account safe by choosing a strong password and not sharing it.</p>

<h2>6. Children’s Privacy</h2>
<p>Our services are not intended for users under 16. We do not knowingly collect data from minors. If you believe we have inadvertently collected a child’s information, please contact us to have it removed.</p>

<h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this policy to reflect changes in our practices or the law. We’ll post the revised version here with the “Last Updated” date. Continued use signifies your acceptance.</p>

<h2>8. Contact Us</h2>
